# MemState web documentation (`docs-site/`)

Static HTML; **left sidebar** = `js/nav.js`; **`data-doc-page`** on `<body>`; subfolders `architecture/`, `data-model/`, `operations/`, `api/`.

## Required content on every page

Each page must include:

1. **Approach** — design choices and tradeoffs for that area (why this pattern).
2. **How it works internally** — concrete flow: which modules, data paths, and mechanisms (Executor, GraphStore, Kuzu, reasoner, etc.). Stay accurate to `src/memstate/`; avoid dumping source line-by-line.

Add **SVG** or **Mermaid** when a diagram clarifies control or data flow.

## Site map

- `index.html` — product + how this doc maps to packages
- **Architecture/** — overview (SVG), storage (Kuzu schema/connection), reasoning (events + rules), http-stack (routers, deps singletons)
- **Data model/** — overview, fields/history (types & nesting), relationships, **limits-and-config** (Policies, semantic/structural/temporal, env), diagram (Mermaid)
- **Operations/** — run-config (settings), high-level (ingest/query/reasoner/async), low-level (ui_api + snapshot builder)
- **api/index.html** — route map to modules

Update **`js/nav.js`** when adding pages. Root **redirect** HTML files for old flat URLs.

## When code changes

Diff `src/` for behavior changes; update the affected page’s **Approach** / **Internal** sections and any diagrams.
